<P>In Con&s;ideration of this, every Sea|man Sub&s;cribing to the Society, &s;hall Agree to Pay to the Receipt of the &s;aid Office, his <HI>Quota</HI> of the Sum to be Paid, whenever, and as often as &s;uch Claims are made; the Claims to be Enter'd into the Office, and upon &s;ufficient Proof made, the Go|vernors
<PB N="130" REF="145">
to Regulate the Divi&s;ion, and Publi&s;h it in Print.</P>
<P><HI>For Example:</HI></P>
<P>Suppo&s;e 4000 Seamen Sub&s;cribe to this Society, and after Six Months, for no Man &s;hou'd Claim &s;ooner than Six Months, a Merchant's Ship having Engag'd a Privateer, there comes &s;e|veral Claims together: As thus; <TABLE>
