<P>The <HI>Exempts</HI> to be Supernumerary, having a &s;mall Allowance, and main|tain'd in the College till Preferment offer.</P>
<P>The Second College to con&s;i&s;t of <HI>Voluntary Students,</HI> to be taken in after
<PB N="266" REF="281">
a certain Degree of Learning, from among the <HI>Proficients</HI> of the Fir&s;t, or from any other Schools, after &s;uch and &s;uch Limitations of Learning; who &s;tudy at their own Charge, being allow'd certain Privileges; as,<LIST>
<ITEM>Chambers Rent-free, on condition of Re&s;idence.</ITEM>
<ITEM>Commons <HI>gratis,</HI> for certain fix'd terms.</ITEM>
